sentence: Thursday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index reaching a historical high.
The index closed at 5,339.52 up 44.34 for the day.
The index first reached the 5000 mark on 09/21/2016 The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.87 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 2.52 to 1 ratio.
There were 2061 advancers and 819 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 118 stocks reached a 52 week high and 9 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .77% for the day; a total of 37.61 points.
Applied Materials, Inc. ( AMAT ) had the largest percent change down (-.92%) while Liberty Interactive Corporation ( QVCA ) had the largest percent change gain rising 5.11%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .54% for the day; a total of 98.76 points.
Pfizer, Inc. ( PFE ) had the largest percent change down (-.38%) while Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change gain rising 1.36%.
